## 3. Sequence Diagrams

### 3a. Login Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant LP as Login Page
    participant AC as AuthContext
    participant AX as Axios API
    participant BE as Backend (auth.js)
    participant DB as MySQL

    User->>LP: Enter email + password
    LP->>AC: login({ email, password })
    AC->>AX: POST /login
    AX->>BE: { email, password }
    
    BE->>DB: SELECT FROM teachers WHERE email = ?
    alt Teacher found
        DB-->>BE: teacher row
        BE->>BE: bcrypt.compare(password, hash)
    else Not in teachers
        BE->>DB: SELECT FROM students WHERE email = ?
        DB-->>BE: student row
        BE->>BE: bcrypt.compare(password, hash)
    end

    alt Password matches
        BE->>BE: Generate accessToken (JWT, 30min)
        BE->>BE: Generate refreshToken (JWT, 7 days)
        BE->>DB: DELETE old refresh_tokens for user
        BE->>DB: INSERT new refresh_token
        BE-->>AX: { accessToken, role, userType } + Set-Cookie(refreshToken)
        AX-->>AC: response
        AC->>AC: localStorage.setItem(token)
        AC->>AC: setUser(state)
        AC-->>LP: success
        LP->>LP: Navigate to role-based dashboard
    else Password invalid
        BE-->>AX: 401 Invalid credentials
        AX-->>AC: error
        AC-->>LP: toast error
    end
```

### 3b. Token Refresh Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant AX as Axios Interceptor
    participant BE as Backend (auth.js)
    participant DB as MySQL

    AX->>AX: Original request gets 401
    AX->>BE: POST /login/refresh (cookie: refreshToken)
    BE->>BE: jwt.verify(refreshToken)
    BE->>DB: SELECT FROM refresh_tokens WHERE token = ? AND expires_at > NOW()
    
    alt Valid token
        DB-->>BE: session row
        BE->>BE: Verify decoded.userId == session.user_id
        BE->>BE: Sign new accessToken (30min)
        BE-->>AX: { accessToken }
        AX->>AX: Update localStorage
        AX->>AX: Retry original request
    else Invalid/Expired
        BE-->>AX: 401
        AX->>AX: Redirect to /login
    end
```

### 3c. Admin Creates Student

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Admin
    participant FE as AdminDashboard
    participant API as API Layer
    participant BE as Backend (admin.js)
    participant DB as MySQL

    Admin->>FE: Fill student creation form
    FE->>API: POST /admin/create_student
    API->>BE: { first_name, last_name, email, password, department_id, year, semester, academic_year, ... }
    
    BE->>BE: Validate fields + year/semester rules
    BE->>BE: bcrypt.hash(password, 10)
    BE->>DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
    BE->>DB: INSERT INTO students (...)
    DB-->>BE: student_id (insertId)
    BE->>DB: INSERT INTO student_fees (student_id, academic_year, total_fee=85000)
    BE->>DB: SELECT course_id FROM courses WHERE dept=? AND semester=?
    DB-->>BE: matching courses[]
    
    loop Each course
        BE->>DB: INSERT INTO enrollments (student_id, course_id, academic_year)
    end
    
    BE->>DB: COMMIT
    BE-->>API: 201 { message, student_id }
    API-->>FE: success
    FE->>Admin: Toast "Student created"
```

### 3d. Faculty Takes Attendance

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Faculty
    participant FE as FacultyDashboard
    participant API as API Layer
    participant BE as Backend (teacher.js)
    participant DB as MySQL

    Faculty->>FE: Select course + date
    FE->>API: POST /teacher/attendance/session
    API->>BE: { course_id, session_date }
    BE->>DB: Verify teacher owns course
    BE->>DB: Get academic_year from enrollments
    BE->>DB: INSERT INTO attendance_sessions
    DB-->>BE: session_id
    BE-->>FE: { session_id }

    FE->>API: GET /teacher/attendance/session/:session_id/students
    API->>BE: request
    BE->>DB: SELECT active enrolled students
    DB-->>BE: students[]
    BE-->>FE: { students }

    Faculty->>FE: Mark each student present/absent
    FE->>API: POST /teacher/attendance/submit
    API->>BE: { session_id, attendance[] }
    BE->>DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
    BE->>DB: INSERT INTO attendance_records (batch)
    BE->>DB: COMMIT
    BE-->>FE: "Attendance submitted successfully"
```

### 3e. Student Dashboard Load

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Student
    participant FE as StudentDashboard
    participant API as API Layer
    participant BE as Backend (student.js)
    participant DB as MySQL

    Student->>FE: Navigate to dashboard
    FE->>API: GET /student/dashboard
    API->>BE: Authorization: Bearer <token>
    BE->>BE: authenticate + authorize("student")
    
    par Parallel DB Queries
        BE->>DB: SELECT profile FROM students
        BE->>DB: SELECT enrolled subjects (JOIN enrollments + courses)
        BE->>DB: SELECT subject-wise attendance (JOIN attendance_sessions + records)
        BE->>DB: SELECT overall attendance
        BE->>DB: SELECT fee record FROM student_fees
        BE->>DB: SELECT timetable (JOIN timetable + time_slots + courses + teachers)
    end

    DB-->>BE: All results
    BE-->>API: { profile, subjects, attendance_by_subject, overall_attendance, feeRecord, timetablerows }
    API-->>FE: dashboard data
    
    FE->>FE: Render ProfileCard
    FE->>FE: Render SubjectsCard
    FE->>FE: Render AttendanceBarSection
    FE->>FE: Render FeeCard
    FE->>FE: Render TimetableTable
```

